      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Start/End frame chaining (10s windows):\n\n- Segment 1 uses frame1 -> frame2\n- Segment 2 uses frame2 -> frame3 (if frame3 exists)\n- If frame3 is absent, leave segment 2 end_frame empty\n\nHow to run:\n1) Fill SCRIPT / BRIEF / NEGATIVE\n2) Run LLM branch\n3) Copy Preview #1 to Kling segment 1 prompt\n4) Copy Preview #2 to Kling segment 2 prompt\n5) For segment 2, connect frame3 only when generated; otherwise keep end_frame empty\n\nScaling beyond 20s:\n- Generate frame4, frame5, ... every new 10s\n- Duplicate segment-2 Kling block pattern: start=frameN, end=frameN+1 (or empty if missing)\n\nImportant:\n- In this JSON, KlingStartEndFrameNode keeps template default mode string. In Comfy UI switch it to Kling 3.0 + Multi-Scene Auto options available in your installed node version."
      ]
    },
